        <name>task</name>
        <reimplements refid="class_task_1a1951102653a5e603f2131b33d7636232">task</reimplements>
        <param>
          <type>void</type>
        </param>
        <briefdescription>
<para><ref refid="struct_adxl37x" kindref="compound">Adxl37x</ref> task function. </para>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para><hruler/>
</para>
<para>The task function directly enter the endless loop and wait for messages. Task wakes up when a message is in the mailbox and read the message by calling mailbox read method which returns the pointer pElem to the message. All expected messages will be handled, in case of an unexpected message an error debug message will be triggered. Finally the message will be released by calling class <ref refid="class_pool_elem" kindref="compound">PoolElem</ref> method free, if the pointer pElem is not explicitly set to 0. <linebreak/>
 <linebreak/>
<bold>Message Handling:</bold> <linebreak/>
<itemizedlist>
<listitem><para>eHwReport: Request a HW status report. The message will be forwarded to <ref refid="struct_adxl37x" kindref="compound">Adxl37x</ref> task. Pointer to the pool element will be set to 0 to prevent the releasing of the message back to the pool.</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>eHwStatusAdxl37x: Status indication from <ref refid="struct_adxl37x" kindref="compound">Adxl37x</ref> task. Error counter will be reset to 0, message payload will be translated in HW metrics structure by calling function HandleHwStatusAdxl37x and this structure will be send to data manager task by call of funtion report. </para>
</listitem></itemizedlist>
</para>
        </detaileddescription>
        <inbodydescription>
        </inbodydescription>
